One person has was killed and two others injured after a head-on collision on the R43 near Baken hoogte in Hermanus in the Western Cape on Sunday. According to Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa, a driver of a car died after colliding with a bakkie. A passenger in the car, and the driver of the bakkie sustained severe injuries.   GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android or iPhone. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW New